  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ecovida Agroecology Network: Strengthening Rural Social Fabric by Building Food Sovereignty</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With many family farms, the three states of Southern Brazil have maintained resistance to the agricultural model imposed by the green revolution. The Ecovida Agroecology Network was created in 1998 as a result of efforts to coordinate the resistance work. Development of participatory certification and public policy making resulted from the coordination, but the Network is currently facing two major challenges: the need to revive their operational dynamics and negotiating capacity; and, the need to adapt to the newly enacted National Law on Organic Agriculture. The present project is seeking support to work with the 270 grassroots organizations in its 24 regional nuclei, with local, regional and general meetings, plus the ongoing work of enlivening the Network. 720 original families will benefit, as well as 2,280 by passing on the gift.</narrative>
  </description>
